Gbgs hamn-arb :kont. 22-35, dir. där sed. 35. Led. av stadsfullm., hamnstyr., löne- o. tjänstendn, ordf. i Sv. flottans res :-off:förb. v. krets. RVO, FFrK, Pro-PatrGM, EmmeryM.
translated: Holmberg, Carl Jacob (Cay), naval captain, director, Gothenburg, born March 28, 1890 in Varberg to manufacturer Olof H. and Anna Mariana Björnberg. Married to Lilly Bengtsson in the 1920s. Children: Lilian born in 1923, married Totting in Karlskrona, Karna born in 1931, Cay born in 1933, Joien born in 1935, Urciilla born in 1937, and Ulif born in 1942. Cecilia Marianne born in 1945. Studied at Varberg's commercial high school and Axelson's commercial institute, obtained navigation officer's certificate in 1910, naval captain's certificate in 1911, and reserve officer's certificate in 1912. Served at sea from 1905 to 1912, then worked as a navigation officer and commanding officer on ships owned by Rederi A-B Transatlantic from 1912 to 1922. He worked as an inspector at Gothenburg's harbor labor office from 1922 to 1935, and was a director there from 1935 onwards. He was a member of the city council, the port board, the salary and employment committee, and chairman of the Swedish Navy's reserve officer association in the district. He was awarded RVO, FFrK, Pro-PatrGM, and EmmeryM honors.

structured.description: Carl Jacob (Cay) Holmberg was a Swedish naval captain and director born on March 28, 1890 in Varberg to manufacturer Olof H. and Anna Mariana Björnberg. He obtained a navigation officer's certificate in 1910, a naval captain's certificate in 1911, and a reserve officer's certificate in 1912. He was married to Lilly Bengtsson in the 1920s and they had seven children. He worked as a navigation officer and commanding officer on ships owned by Rederi A-B Transatlantic from 1912 to 1922. He then worked as an inspector at Gothenburg's harbor labor office from 1922 to 1935, and was a director there from 1935 onwards. Holmberg was also a member of the city council, the port board, the salary and employment committee, and was chairman of the Swedish Navy's reserve officer association in the district. He was awarded RVO, FFrK, Pro-PatrGM, and EmmeryM honors.
